SIMPLE: sinner
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Sinner
<hw>Sin"ner</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>One who has sinned;
especially, one who has sinned without repenting; hence, a persistent
and incorrigible transgressor; one condemned by the law of
God.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Sinner</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Sinner
<hw>Sin"ner</hw>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <def>To act as a sinner.</def>
<mark>[Humorous]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Whether the charmer <qex>sinner</qex> it or saint it.</q>
<rj><qau>Pope.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Sinneress</ent>⟦br⟧
